do you use closed captioning even though you aren't deaf or hard of hearing yes i do i like to see the dialogue especially when people have accents and i might miss something it's handy when i am on the phone and i still want to see the news i hate to watch a movie and miss a phrase it can affect the whole movie usually i can rewind and hear it again but closed captioning is such a time saver i like foreign films and the subtitles don't bother me a bit Closed captioning Subtitle Hearing impairment Notable lines in the Star Wars series Teletext Have I Got News For You Dubbing (filmmaking) Roger Ebert's most hated films Anime Deaf culture Hiberno-English Innocence: Ghost in the Shell The Jazz Singer Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind English English Back to the Future Contemporary culture of South Korea The Passion of the Jew Ron and Fez Telecommunications Relay Service Superman III The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Katie Holmes Rowan & Martin's Laugh-In EIA-708 Fire Walk With Me Digital television Quebec French All your base are belong to us Backward message Telecommunications devices for the deaf Humphrey Bogart Special Broadcasting Service Deaf 10 Things I Hate About You I'm Sorry, I'll Read That Again CBC Television Shaggy dog story British National Party Non-native pronunciations of English Wall Street (movie) Time Out of Mind Film soundtrack Ann Coulter DVD Russian joke Aladdin (1992 film) The Shining (film) Katakana On-Line Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences Metcard Social rule Red Dwarf British small press comics Sign language Book of Isaiah Donovan Telephone booth Angels in America Motion picture rating system Jackass: The Movie Slayers Meta-reference Sin City Glossary of medical terms related to communications disorders The Rocky and Bullwinkle Show Ken Jennings Culture of the United States Scream (film) Speech synthesis Team America: World Police Audio commentary (DVD) Little Britain The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy British Sign Language Craig David T